<TITLE> CCDM formed for 2007-8 season </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 5 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) Wednesday announced a five-member committee for the Cricket Committee of Dhaka Metropolis (CCDM) for 2007-2008 season. The Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) earlier formed the CCDM with Gazi Ashraf Hossain Lipu and Feroz Ahmed as chairman and co-chairman respectively. Members of the committee are Tarikul Islam Titu and deputy commissioner (Mirpur zone, Dhaka Metropolitan Police). The CCDM named the coordinators of the premier, first, second, third divisions and third division qualifying for the 2007-2008 season. They are MA Kabir (premier division coordinator), Abu Selim Babla (first division coordinator), Jobair Kabir Chowdhury Nipu (second division coordinator), Amin Khan (third division coordinator) M Humayun Kabir Ripon (third division qualifying coordinator). However, Mohidur Rahman Miraj will play the role of coordinator for the pending third division qualifying for 2006-2007. The CCDM will sit on Friday to discuss the premier division's relegation league (season 2006-2007) at the BCB office at Bangabandhu National Stadium. Three clubs of Brothers Union, City Club and Indira Road KC will play the relegation league, but the date of the league is yet to be fixed. 
